<br>
Actually, this patch does basically nothing more than provide free extra exp for the people who really liked to group, aside from perhaps increasing the pool of (unskilled) people who may now wish to instead of soloing, and at the cost of increasing the competition for those group-required camping spots.  Pennies from heaven, as if the group exp bonus wasn't enough... begs the question why that wasn't just increased instead doesn't it?<br>
<br>
It's a hardcore nerf to soloers without question.<br>
<br>
For the folks in between, or who take lots of deaths during raids (pullers, crowd control, MTs) it's a nasty thing too- no more heading to FG for a few hours to make up exp lost during a trip to NToV or Ssra cycles. <br>
<br>
What SHOULD have been done was to balance things such that the actual risk of an encounter factored into the exp gained, but that's a really non-trivial thing to do.  I really think they overdid it, nerfing exp by over half is just a bit much...<br>
<br>
